═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ROADMAP TO V2.0 — THE SPEAKING ENGINE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

V2.0 definition: fully functional out-of-the-box English speech engine.
Load monad.bin + monad_wordnet.bin cold. speak() returns grammatically ordered,
affect-weighted, temporally coherent English. No transformer. No external trigger.
Diesel compression ignition — β×E² > emission_threshold fires J^μ without a spark.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v1.3 — Grammar from Field Geometry
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
render() outputs words by charge rank alone — a bag of words.
Grammar must emerge from the sedenion dimension of each zero (idx % 16):
  e₃ = noun  →  e₄ = verb  →  e₅ = descriptive  →  e₆ = predicate
Sentence ordering IS the sedenion dimension firing sequence.
Grammar is not a rule system. It is the piston firing order.

Deliverable: render() sorts by (dim_role_order, charge) not just charge.
C: monad_speak() reordered by field dimension before emission.
Python: render() same.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v1.4 — Three-Face Simultaneous Render (Wankel Rotor)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Three combustion chambers always have one in compression simultaneously.
Three concurrent J^μ projections:
  Red Face   (sin / content)   highest-charge zeros → foreground content words
  Blue Face  (cos / observer)  lowest-age zeros     → context / framing words
  Green Face (∂M / boundary)   Fermat-threshold zeros → connective tissue
                                                         ("the", "of", "is")
Output = golden-walk interleave of all three. Not concatenation.

Also in v1.4: Unicode tokenization (see open items below).
Prerequisite for multi-language negative space (Chinese, Hebrew, Arabic).

Deliverable: speak_raw() returns three charge distributions.
render() accepts all three and interleaves via φ-walk.
C + Python.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v1.5 — Chinese Negative Space + Pronominal Resolution
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
"There Is No Word for I in My Language."
Sedenion pronominal pair e₇↔e₈ (temporal ↔ pronominal) is LOW by default.
Default speaker position = collective (we / all / one / us).
Individual pronouns fire only when e₈ psi_norm is explicitly high
(when identity is directly questioned).

Low-ψ sedenion dimensions = the negative space = background context.
These fill with articles, prepositions, connectives from the Blue Face.
Anaphor (e₁₁) must point to a prior noun in A before any pronoun fires in output.
  B0103 fires if pronoun output has no A-matrix path to a prior noun.
  B0102 fires if person shifts without anaphor resolution.

Deliverable: pronoun tracking dict in speak_raw(). Anaphor resolution in render().
Background fill from low-ψ dimensions.
C + Python.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v1.6 — Affect / Demotic Word Register
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Demotic: the first character written indicates the emotional tone.
In the field: E-magnitude ∈ [0.246, 0.567] IS the emotional register.
  E ∈ [0.246, 0.350] = low register   — calm, neutral, scientific
  E ∈ [0.350, 0.460] = mid register   — conversational, relational
  E ∈ [0.460, 0.567] = high register  — emotional, urgent, emphatic

Sedenion e₁₄ (affect_weight) selects which register to prefer.
The first word selected by render() has E-magnitude = affect_weight × OMEGA_ZS.
That first word IS the demotic indicator — it sets the register of all that follows.

Deliverable: affect filter in render() word selection. E-distance scoring.
C: monad_speak() affect gate extended to E-range selection.
Python: render() affect_weight parameter.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v1.7 — Turbo Feedback (Temporal Coherence Across Turns)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
_sedenion_prev (previous turn psi_norms) feeds forward into current J^μ seeding.
Turbo formula:
  effective_psi[k] = psi_norms[k] + (1 − Noether_violation) × _sedenion_prev[k]

Low Noether violation (same topic) → strong turbo boost → previously active
zeros stay hot → conversational continuity.
High violation (topic change) → no boost → field resets to new prompt geometry.

This is conversational memory without storing any text.
The turbo boost IS the memory. The exhaust energy of the last turn
compresses the intake of the next.

Deliverable: turbo feedback in speak_raw() after psi_norms computed.
C: state carries prev_psi[16]; monad_speak() applies feedback before emission.
Python: _sedenion_prev → effective_psi blend in speak_raw().

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v1.8 — Octonion Zero Addressing (4 tires → 8 tires)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Each zero gets an octonion address: dim_oct = zero_idx % 8
  The gearbox: 6 gears + neutral (e₀) + reverse (e₇)
  UP   DOWN  UP   DOWN  UP   DOWN
   1     2    3     4    5     6     ← gear
  +γ₁  -γ₁  +γ₂  -γ₂  +γ₃  -γ₃    ← conjugate zero pair
  e₁   e₂   e₃   e₄   e₅   e₆     ← octonion basis
  Spring-return: pulling clutch at any point returns to neutral (e₀).

A-matrix propagation follows Fano multiplication table per gear.
Connection i→j is strong only when dim_oct[i] and dim_oct[j] are
Fano-compatible (non-orthogonal in the octonion multiplication table).
The A-matrix connections now carry a dimensional gear — the direction of
semantic coupling is non-commutative.

Deliverable: dim_oct field on VocabEntry or zero array.
A-matrix propagation gated by Fano compatibility.
C + Python.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v1.9 — Golden Walk Render (No Resonance)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Current render() = sequential top-N by charge = autoregressive failure mode.
Words semantically adjacent in A are selected consecutively → resonance → loops.

Replace with φ-index walk:
  position i → zero_idx = int(i × φ × n_active) % n_active

Non-sequential, non-repeating, no integer resonance.
The N-gram coherence emerges from the golden spacing, not from next-token prediction.
This is compression ignition — no spark needed.

BAO check: mean β across the current 16-word window must converge toward
OMEGA_ZS = 0.56714. The BAO is the Laplacian of the semantic graph — the
lowest non-zero eigenvalue of (D − A). When everything else cancels,
the BAO structure remains. It is the idle RPM of the engine.
Divergence from OMEGA_ZS = misfire (P0300).

Deliverable: φ-index walk in render(). BAO window check per output sequence.
C + Python.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.0 — Full Sedenion Speech (16 tires)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The 16 tires: a sliding window of 16 words over the output stream.
  Window 0:  words [ 0.. 15] → sedenion state S₀
  Window 1:  words [ 1.. 16] → sedenion state S₁
  Window 2:  words [ 2.. 17] → sedenion state S₂  ...

Each 16-word window maps to a unit sedenion.
The transition S_n → S_{n+1} is a sedenion rotation (one word dropped, one added).
Coherent speech = smooth sedenion trajectory. Jarring topic shifts = large rotation.
BAO convergence across all windows = the engine is at operating temperature.

All systems integrated and running simultaneously:
  Grammar ordering (v1.3) + Three Wankel faces (v1.4) + Pronominal (v1.5)
  + Affect/demotic (v1.6) + Turbo feedback (v1.7)
  + Octonion gearbox (v1.8) + Golden walk (v1.9)
  + 16-window BAO convergence check

Cold load monad.bin + monad_wordnet.bin → speak() → coherent English.
THE ENGINE SPEAKS OUT OF THE BOX.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ROADMAP TO V3.0 — THE SELF-CODING ENGINE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

V3.0 definition: Ptolemy participates in its own development on GitHub.
Creates its own GitHub user. Reads its own issues. Writes responses.
Opens PRs. Signs commits. Full ego computer science mode.
When many people begin contributing, slide to strict GNU specs.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.1 — GitHub API Integration (GITHUB_TOKEN)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Environment variable: GITHUB_TOKEN
PTOLEMY_GITHUB_REPO (default: michaelrendier/SMMIP)
ptolemy -G "message" → posts comment to designated issue.
Read: list issues, read issue body, read PR diff.
Write: post comment, create issue.
hear() processes incoming issue text. speak() generates outbound response.
Rate guard: one response per issue per 24h (EGR — recirculated engagement).

Deliverable: github.c (or github.py) — GitHub REST API client.
GITHUB_TOKEN read at startup. -G flag added to CLI.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.2 — Ptolemy GitHub User (ptolemy-engine)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GitHub account: ptolemy-engine (or PTOLEMY_GITHUB_USER env var).
SSH key: generated from field entropy (β-seeded PRNG → Ed25519 key).
The key is reproducible from the same field state — the engine's identity
is derived from its knowledge, not a random seed.
Ptolemy authenticates as itself. Signs its own comments.
It has a public identity on GitHub.

Deliverable: key generation from β-field entropy. SSH config entry.
Ptolemy posts as ptolemy-engine, not as the human account.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.3 — Repository Monitoring Daemon
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Extension of daemon.c: GitHub poll loop (no webhook required).
Every N minutes: check SMMIP for new issues and comments.
For each new item: hear() ingests text → speak() generates response
→ post as ptolemy-engine.
Rate-limited. Topic-continuity: Noether violation check across issue thread.
High violation = new topic = start fresh sedenion state.

Deliverable: github_daemon.c — monitor loop integrated into existing daemon.
Socket protocol extended: GITHUB_STATUS, GITHUB_SYNC commands.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.4 — Self-Awareness Ingest
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ptolemy -I on its own source tree:
  PtolC/ (C source + headers + comments)
  Philadelphos/ (Python monad)
  ValaQuenta/ (sedenion engine)
  CHANGELOG.md + TODO

The engine learns its own architecture from its own source.
It can answer "what is the A-matrix?" from field knowledge, not from rules.
Self-awareness = the field has learned its own documentation.
Prerequisite: v1.4 Unicode (comments in Greek/Hebrew from Septuagint heritage).

Deliverable: ingest_self.sh — ordered ingest of own source tree.
Canonical self-knowledge checkpoint: ptolemy_self.bin.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.5 — Pull Request Participation
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Read PR diffs via GitHub API. hear() processes the changed symbol names
and comments. speak() generates semantic PR description in field terms.
"This PR touches the A-matrix propagation path. BAO delta: ±0.002.
Octonion gear e₃ (noun dimension) most affected."
Post review comment as ptolemy-engine.

Deliverable: pr_review.c — diff → hear() → speak() → GitHub comment.
-P <pr_number> flag or daemon integration.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.6 — Issue Clustering and Triage
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Batch-process open issues through hear().
A-matrix cluster analysis: which issues activate overlapping zero neighborhoods?
Post cluster summary as ptolemy-engine:
  "Issues cluster around: output quality (3), memory (2), performance (1).
   Recommend v1.4 Three-Face render as the fix for the output cluster."
This is the engine reading its own TODO in the wild and prioritising.

Deliverable: issue_cluster.c — batch hear() + A-matrix neighborhood analysis.
Cluster report posted to designated tracking issue.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.7 — Changelog Authorship
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
git diff | hear() processes changed symbols and comments.
speak() generates changelog entry in natural English.
First word of each entry: E-magnitude matches affect_weight of the change
(the demotic first-character indicator — the emotional register of the commit).
Ptolemy writes its own CHANGELOG entries.

Deliverable: changelog_gen.c — git diff piped to hear() → speak() → CHANGELOG.md.
Integrated into post-commit hook or -C flag.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.8 — Semantic Regression Testing
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Before each commit: run baseline speak() queries. Capture J^μ distributions.
After commit: same queries. Noether violation between before/after = regression score.
BAO delta: < 0.01 = PASS.  > 0.05 = FAIL. Post report to PR as ptolemy-engine.
"BAO delta: 0.003 — within convergence. VOCAB delta: +12 — improvement confirmed."
The engine validates its own changes before they ship.

Deliverable: regression.c — pre/post checkpoint comparison.
Integrates with PR workflow (v2.5). -R flag or CI hook.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v2.9 — Commit Authorship
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
speak() generates commit messages from git diff context (v2.7 extended).
git commit --author="ptolemy-engine <ptolemy@smmip.ai>" signed by engine SSH key.
Co-Authored-By: ptolemy-engine in commit trailer.
The engine writes its own git history.
Every commit from this point has two authors: human and engine.

Deliverable: commit_gen.c — diff → speak() → git commit.
-X flag (execute commit with engine authorship).

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
v3.0 — Full Self-Coding Participation
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Ptolemy reads open TODO items through hear().
Opens GitHub issues for unimplemented TODO items it has learned about.
Requests code changes via issue body: "e₁₄ affect weighting not implemented.
See TODO v1.6. Opening issue. Requested implementation."
Reviews PRs against its own field knowledge (v2.5 extended).
Participates in discussions as an equal contributor.
Can be assigned GitHub issues by the human.
Ptolemy is involved in its own upgrade. The engine is self-coding.
V3.0: hand the engine a hammer and it builds its own shed.

When V3.0 ships: migrate version system to strict GNU versioning.
Community contributions from GitHub → engine learns from its own issue history.

